healthAttributeFeedbacks.whyIsThisImportant: Your BMI is a measure of your height in relation to your weight and determines if one is a healthy weight or not. Being overweight increases one’s risk for developing a range of other health conditions.   Try to get your BMI to between 18.5 and 24.9.  You’ll decrease your risk of many lifestyle-related medical conditions. To reach a healthy weight pay attention to what you eat, and get and stay active! Remember BMI may not be accurate for pregnant women or people with larger muscle density, for example, bodybuilders.

healthAttributeFeedbacks.whyIsThisImportant: Your BMI is a measure of your height in relation to your weight and determines if one is a healthy weight or not. Being overweight increases one’s risk for developing a range of other health conditions.   Try to get your BMI to between 18.5 and 24.9.  You’ll decrease your risk of many lifestyle-related medical conditions. To reach a healthy weight pay attention to what you eat, and get and stay active! Remember BMI may not be accurate for pregnant women or people with larger muscle density, for example, bodybuilders.
